> Our iconic firecracker sauce—creamy, spicy, sweet, and savory—elevates tender
> turkey meatloaves to delicious new heights. The loaves are glazed with an
> umami-rich soy-ginger sauce and roasted alongside broccoli and zucchini. A
> final drizzle of firecracker sauce completes the meal.

Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and
preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{1}(cut into bite-size pieces) into bite-size pieces if necessary.
Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); lay flat and cut on
a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Toss broccoli and zucchini on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle
of @cooking oil{a large drizzle}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4, spread veggies
out across entire sheet.)

> TIP: For easier cleanup, line baking sheet with foil before adding veggies.

== Meatloaves ==

In a #medium bowl{}, gently combine @ground turkey{10%oz}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the
@stir-fry sauce{3%oz}, @water{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), @salt{}, and
@pepper{}.

Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

== Roasting ==

Place meatloaves on opposite side of baking sheet from veggies; brush tops of
meatloaves with remaining stir-fry sauce. (For 4 servings, place meatloaves on
a second baking sheet.)

Roast on middle rack until meatloaves are cooked through and veggies are browned
and tender, ~{22-25%minutes}. (For 4, roast veggies on top rack and meatloaves
on middle rack, swapping rack positions halfway through.)

== Firecracker Sauce ==

While meatloaves and veggies roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine
@mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, @ponzu sauce{6%ml},
@water{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

== Serving ==

Divide meatloaves and veggies between plates; drizzle meatloaves with as much
firecracker sauce as you like. Serve with any remaining firecracker sauce on the
side.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.